{{Infobox MP | name = Syed Essa Noori | honorific-suffix = |image = | office =Member of the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] | term_start = 13 August 2013 |term_end = 31 May 2018 |constituency = [[Constituency NA-272|NA-272 (Kech-cum-Gwadar)]] | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1953 | 1 | 1 }} | birth_place = |nationality = Pakistani |party = [[Balochistan National Party (Mengal)]] }}
'''Syed Essa Noori''' ({{Lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|سید عیسیٰ نوری}}}}; born 1 January 1953) is a Pakistani politician who had been a member of the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]], from August 2013 to May 2018.
==Early life== He was born on 1 January 1953.<ref name="pildat/dob">{{cite web|title=Detail Information|url=http://www.pildat.org/mna/rsDetail.asp?detid=272|accessdate=11 July 2017|date=21 April 2014|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140421152525/http://www.pildat.org/mna/rsDetail.asp?detid=272|archivedate=21 April 2014|df=}}</ref>
==Political career==
He was elected to the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] as a candidate of [[Balochistan National Party (Mengal)]] (BNP-M) from [[Constituency NA-272|Constituency NA-272 (Kech-cum-Gwadar)]] in by-election held in August 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=ROs yet to send key documents to ECP|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1150785|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=14 December 2014|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307123636/https://www.dawn.com/news/1150785|archivedate=7 March 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=PML-N bagged 119pc more votes than in 2008|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1012824|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=22 May 2013|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304194129/https://www.dawn.com/news/1012824|archivedate=4 March 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=MPs showed lack of interest in NA working in 4 years: Fafen|url=http://nation.com.pk/newspaper-picks/23-Oct-2016/mps-showed-lack-of-interest-in-na-working-in-4-years-fafen|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=The Nation|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307045510/http://nation.com.pk/newspaper-picks/23-Oct-2016/mps-showed-lack-of-interest-in-na-working-in-4-years-fafen|archivedate=7 March 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Jobs quota: PM declines request to fill Balochistan posts - The Express Tribune|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/678250/jobs-quota-pm-declines-request-to-fill-balochistan-posts/|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=The Express Tribune|date=3 March 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307050936/https://tribune.com.pk/story/678250/jobs-quota-pm-declines-request-to-fill-balochistan-posts/|archivedate=7 March 2017|df=}}</ref> He received 15,835 votes and defeated Muhammad Yasin Baloch, a candidate of [[National Party (Pakistan)|National Party]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2013 election result|url=https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/General%20Elections%202013%20report/Election%20Report%202013%20Volume-II.pdf|publisher=ECP|accessdate=12 May 2018|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180201140612/https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/General%20Elections%202013%20report/Election%20Report%202013%20Volume-II.pdf|archivedate=1 February 2018|df=}}</ref>
